# Architecture

System shape and runtime boundaries for Pi Discord Threads.

## Shape

Capture the project architecture here as it becomes clear.

## Runtime boundaries

List durable process, data, UI, and agent boundaries here.

## Effect architecture evaluation

2026-06-17: `pi-discord-threads` does not currently use Effect. The local Effect source mirror for evaluation is at `.agent_sources/github.com/Effect-TS/effect` and is ignored from git.

Effect is a good fit for reliability-heavy daemon seams: process lifecycle, Discord/Inngest/Redis resource scopes, retries/timeouts, typed errors, dependency injection, and test clocks/fakes. It is not worth pulling into tiny command aliases or pure parsing/formatting helpers.

Recommendation: do not rewrite the bridge wholesale. If the tool keeps growing, adopt Effect at the edge-to-core seams first: `run-control`, `link-ingest-status-bridge`, `SecretResolver`/config, and `PiRuntimeManager` lifecycle. Keep Discord handlers thin and keep simple pure functions plain TypeScript.

## Thread run lifecycle

2026-06-18: `discord-bot.ts` was already too large to keep absorbing run lifecycle rules. Put finite run-state decisions in `src/thread-run-state.ts` using XState v5, then let Discord code route/render and Pi runtime execute.

Current boundary:

- `src/thread-run-state.ts`: state machine and prompt-start/queue decisions.
- `src/pi-runtime.ts`: detects live Pi runtime/session state and queues into active sessions instead of starting duplicate turns.
- `src/discord-bot.ts`: creates/updates Discord messages, records registry metadata, and reacts to completed vs queued runtime results.

Rule: new lifecycle states/transitions belong in `thread-run-state.ts` first. Do not keep adding scattered `status`/`activeRun` conditionals to `discord-bot.ts`.

## XState lifecycle modeling

2026-06-18: Use XState v5 as the canonical modeling tool for finite daemon and runtime lifecycle truth. Effect remains the resource/fiber/scope layer; XState owns named states, events, guards, parallel regions, and invoked actors where lifecycle ambiguity causes bugs.

Source receipts: installed `xstate@5.32.1`; local XState declarations expose `setup(...).createMachine(...)`, `fromPromise`, `fromCallback`, `invoke`, `parallel`, `final`, `history`, `guards`, and actor cleanup semantics. Use the installed package source/declarations as implementation canon before relying on memory or examples.

Preferred XState v5 idiom for new machines:

- define machines with `setup({ types, actors, actions, guards }).createMachine(...)`;
- model side effects as invoked actors, not anonymous async `entry` handlers;
- use `fromPromise` for bounded startup/shutdown steps;
- use `fromCallback` for long-lived subscriptions, process signals, Discord gateway lifetime, and cleanup handles;
- use parallel regions when roles can be independently ready/degraded/stopping, especially `bot`, `worker`, and `reconcile`;
- keep domain transitions in small machine modules, with Discord/Redis/Pi adapters executing effects at the edges.

Candidate XState surfaces:

1. `AppLifecycleMachine`: process startup, role readiness, signal handling, drain, shutdown, terminal failure.
2. `ThreadRunMachine`: per-thread prompt/queue/running/interrupted/final states; already started in `src/thread-run-state.ts`.
3. `RunWorkerMachine`: Redis job claim, lease heartbeat, prompt execution, finalization, ACK/reclaim/fail-safe.
4. `PiSessionMachine`: idle/running/compacting/retrying/aborting/stale-stream recovery for one durable Pi session.
5. `LinkIngestStatusMachine`: accepted/classified/archived/extracted/summarized/ready/indexed/failed/send-failed projection.

Do not turn every pure helper into a machine. Use XState where illegal state combinations, retries, cancellation, resource lifetime, or parallel readiness are the real problem.

2026-06-18: Discord HUD/progress rendering now has the first `discord-bot.ts` decomposition seam. Pure Components V2 payload builders live in `src/discord/payloads.ts`; queued/deduped Discord message edits live in `src/discord/message-renderer.ts`; progress render lifecycle lives in `src/discord/progress-hud-machine.ts`. Final assistant output remains a fresh Discord message, while the HUD placeholder persists as an archived terminal card with ESC disabled.

2026-06-18: Discord thread-title lifecycle rules now live in `src/discord/thread-title.ts`. The bot keeps routing and channel lookup, while the module owns placeholder-title replacement, completed-turn evidence capture, conservative title-evaluator cadence, human-title protection, and rename cooldown rules. Regression coverage lives in `scripts/thread-title-lifecycle-regression.test.mjs`.

2026-06-18: Async subagent result publishing now lives in `src/discord/async-subagent-result-bridge.ts`. The module owns temp result polling, result-to-thread matching, formatting, chunking, retry/seen semantics, and unlink-after-publish. `src/discord-bot.ts` keeps Discord channel resolution and final assistant-message recording through a narrow `publish(record, chunks)` adapter. Regression coverage lives in `scripts/async-subagent-result-bridge-regression.test.mjs`.

2026-06-18: Redis worker job claiming now has `src/run-control/worker-machine.ts` as a first XState slice. It models one stream job through `loadingRun -> validatingRun -> loadingActiveRunId -> claimingLease -> executingWithLease -> release/ack|pending|failed`. Busy finalization now leaves the stream job pending without logging an outside-handler failure.

2026-06-18: Leased run execution/finalization now lives in `src/run-control/leased-run-machine.ts`. The worker loop no longer owns heartbeat/input/finalization booleans; the leased-run machine owns heartbeat cleanup, input pump ticking/draining, fresh execution, persisted-finalizing resume, finalization claim routing, duplicate-finalization fail-safe, terminal marking, and active-pointer clearing as named states.

2026-06-18: Worker lane polling now lives in `src/run-control/worker-lane-machine.ts`. Each lane models consumer-group ensure/retry, dequeue, idle heartbeat, per-job handling, and graceful stop as named states. `src/run-control/worker.ts` now only starts/stops lane actors and wires leased-run execution into the lane machine.

## pi-notes boundary

pi-notes renders `.brain/**/*.svx`, auto-imports standard and project-local Brain components, and can route browser Review Batches back to the spawning Pi session when opened through Pi.
